---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { slide } from 'astro:transitions';
---
<Layout title="My Journey :: Collins">
  <main 
    class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8"
    transition:animate={slide({ duration: '0.3s' })}
  >
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-4">My Learning Journey</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-12">
      I believe in the "Ï€-shaped" developer model: broad knowledge of systems combined with deep expertise in specific crafts. This is my map.
    </p>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        The Horizontal Bar: My "Systems" Exploration
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
        This is the curiosity that drives me. I explore the "why" and the "environment" that our code lives in.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <span class="skill-tag">Systems Architecture</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Networking Fundamentals</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Local-First & PWA</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Observability (Logging & Metrics)</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Containerization (Docker)</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">CI/CD Automation</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Modern Auth (WebAuthn)</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Performance Optimization</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        The Vertical Legs: My "Craftsman" Focus
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
        This is my current curriculum. I'm taking a focused pause to build deep, foundational expertise in these specific areas.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li class="craft-item">
          <strong class="font-semibold">Advanced JavaScript & TypeScript:</strong>
          Mastering the language from the ground up, including asynchronous patterns, memory management, and the event loop.
        </li>
        <li class="craft-item">
          <strong class="font-semibold">Data Structures & Algorithms:</strong>
          Moving beyond "vibe-architecting" to write code that is provably efficient and correct.
        </li>
        <li class="craft-item">
          <strong class="font-semibold">Production-Grade Node.js:</strong>
          Re-building my backends from scratch to deeply understand concurrency, streaming, and security best practices.
        </li>
        <li class="craft-item">
          <strong class="font-semibold">UI/UX Principles & Design Systems:</strong>
          Learning the formal rules of design, typography, and interaction to make my personal projects (like Curiosity) as beautiful as they are functional.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .skill-tag {
    @apply text-base font-medium bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 dark:bg-purple-900 dark:text-purple-200 py-2 px-4 rounded-full;
  }
  
  .craft-item {
    @apply p-6 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700;
  }
</style>